Aside from the obvious "it works with alpha2", other
notable changes are that we dropped the fabric-ca-client.

Since 1.0 doesn't support TCerts/Attributes, the CA
was only adding complexity that we couldn't capitalize
on.  Therefore, we now switch to a model where the
ECert is imported directly, rather than translating
a username/password into an ECert via the CA.

[FAB-9327] Support 'build -p' for system chaincode

The 'chaintool build' for system-chaincodes currently has a limitation
where it only supports being run from the CWD of the chaincode.  This
means that the "-p" option cannot be used.

This limitation is due to the execution of the "go list" command as
part of discovering context.  This command must be run in the CWD of
the package we are discovering.  We can enhance chaintool by managing
the CWD while we launch this command and once again support the -p
switch.  This will be important later one when we add broader support
for SCC as part of FAB-9191/FAB-8724.

Fixes FAB-9327

[FAB-9340] Fix SCC support

This patch updates the 'system' platform to support changes
to fabric in the SCC design since chaintool first added
support.

The primary differences are as follows:

1) Code is now generated as a ./vendor under the SCC
2) We dropped custom, package-name based namespacing in favor
   of simple 'hyperledger'.
3) We change the stub registration to simply allocate the
   handler and return, rather than trying to "own" the event-loop.

data.commitMessage:
[FABCT-53] Fix support for referencing embedded types

We add support for referencing types nested within other
definitions.  There were two primary problems:

1) Our EBNF was capturing nested notation as a vector,
e.g. "Foo.MyEnum" was captured as ["Foo" "." "MyEnum"]

2) Our AST validation logic only was designed to handle
inner-to-outer scope.  For the cases where the CCI was
defined to utilize nested messages, our validator needs
to understand to look in both directions (e.g. including
outer-to-inner).  We now define the former as "local scope"
and the latter as "global" scope, and include both dimensions
in the validator.

Fixes FABCT-53

Change-Id: Iba87dfd27b9d65481fb04e0ce993c1c5180deaa9
Signed-off-by: Greg Haskins <gregory.haskins@gmail.com>
